250
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:32,375
Shit, get back. He's with them!

251
00:15:33,916 --> 00:15:35,583
Kid's a Twilight!

252
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,208
[ALL gasp]

253
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:44,541
Damn!

254
00:15:47,375 --> 00:15:49,916
Heh. You're good.

255
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,750
But that don't mean you
can play in my league.

256
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,583
[DELICO]
He's no child.

257
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:57,708
[DOUG]
Hey, Danny Monroe!

258
00:15:57,791 --> 00:16:01,125
I thought you'd have better
bodyguards than these jokers!

259
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,583
[DELICO]
Not good.

260
00:16:02,666 --> 00:16:06,833
Go link up with the
other unit. I'll handle him.

261
00:16:06,916 --> 00:16:08,166
[GANG MEMBER D]
Hey.

262
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:12,416
They're all friggin' monsters.

263
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:13,833
[YANG]
The attack's stopped.

264
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:14,875
Think we may've been too quick

265
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:16,875
to call the Handymen
for back up.

266
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,208
--[phone buzzing]
--Hold on.

267
00:16:21,708 --> 00:16:23,416
Hey, kid.

268
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:24,833
[GANG MEMBER G] You shouldn't
be out here, sport...

269
00:16:24,916 --> 00:16:25,875
Delico, what's up?

270
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:27,958
[DELICO]
Yang! One got away from us!

271
00:16:28,041 --> 00:16:29,583
Young male, looks like a kid.

272
00:16:29,666 --> 00:16:31,416
Watch out for the little punk!

273
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,416
Don't let him get near the boss!

274
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,416
He's a Twilight!

275
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,458
[gasps]

276
00:16:44,416 --> 00:16:45,625
[MONROE]
Hmm.

277
00:16:45,708 --> 00:16:48,875
S'one agile little fucker.
Ya screwed up, Yang.

278
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:50,500
I'm sorry, sir.

279
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:54,916
[MONROE] I'm worried this
twerp's gonna spoil dinner.

280
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,333
I wanna show up with
you guys not dead.

281
00:16:57,416 --> 00:16:58,291
You can take him, right?

282
00:16:58,375 --> 00:16:59,375
[YANG, DIEGO, MILES]
Yes, sir!

283
00:17:01,708 --> 00:17:03,000
[NICOLAS sniffs]

284
00:17:04,458 --> 00:17:06,833
What? Why'd you stop?

285
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:08,291
Dammit, Nic!

286
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:11,583
Ugh. That's ripe.

287
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,166
Hey, he was one of Monroe's men.

288
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:19,833
What're you thinking about
these super clean cuts?

289
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:22,500
Looks like something
your blade--

290
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,750
Ah, hell. Is it?

291
00:17:25,958 --> 00:17:27,958
So, uh. Hey, Chad.

292
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:30,458
Can we talk about
what Worick did?

293
00:17:30,541 --> 00:17:32,000
This smells fishy.

294
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:33,208
[CODY]
Huh?

295
00:17:33,291 --> 00:17:35,625
Reminds me of all the crap

296
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:39,125
that led up to the Twilight
hunts 15 years ago.

297
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:40,916
[DOUG]
Aw, dammit!

298
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,958
I just stole this hoodie, too!

299
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:46,375
Now I know why they call him
"Gunslinger Danny."

300
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:49,166
Sure he's an old man, but his
aim's still fresh as ever.

301
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:50,625
--[MILES] That voice.
--[DIEGO] It's him.

302
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:53,583
I'm so flattered by
your kind words.

303
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:55,000
[chuckles]

304
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:57,291
Y'know, I find it hard to
believe that in this city

305
00:17:57,375 --> 00:18:00,291
where the Three Laws've
been in effect for 20 years,

306
00:18:00,375 --> 00:18:04,000
we still have to put up with
dumb little shits like you.

307
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,416
Oh, excuse me.

308
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:09,333
I mean with rebellious,
acrobatic daredevils like you.

309
00:18:09,416 --> 00:18:11,750
You're startin' to
piss me off, dude.

310
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,875
If I hadn't promised to
bring you back whole,

311
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:15,416
I'd chop off that
ugly head of yours

312
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:18,291
and shove it right up
your wrinkly old ass.

313
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:19,833
Terrifyin', truly.

314
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:23,625
[DOUG] Well don't try cryin'
to me later, you fuckin' Normal!

315
00:18:25,041 --> 00:18:27,625
[PUNK D]
Awesome. He's decimatin' 'em.

316
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:30,333
Man, we shoulda just hired
a Twilight from the jump

317
00:18:30,416 --> 00:18:31,916
and been done with it.

318
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,166
[PUNK C] But are ya sure it's
cool we went to a guy like him

319
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:35,500
without askin' first?

320
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:36,708
If the boss finds out--

321
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:38,666
[PUNK D] He won't if
we keep our mouths shut.

322
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:39,916
And once Monroe's in the bag,

323
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,500
the Cristiano family
will be a breeze.

324
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,125
Hey, sweet-cheeks.

325
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:52,375
--[thudding]
--[PUNKS groaning]

326
00:18:56,666 --> 00:19:00,458
You don't mind if I ask you
a couple questions, now do you?

327
00:19:01,958 --> 00:19:03,541
[MAID A]
Young Master?

328
00:19:03,625 --> 00:19:05,916
Young Master Wallace?

329
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:10,166
Sheesh, that boy is too much.
I swear, he must be defective.

330
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:13,875
[WALLACE] I'm defective?
He's the one who's defective.

331
00:19:13,958 --> 00:19:17,708
If he can't hear, how's he
supposed to protect me?

332
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:19,291
Makes no sense.

333
00:19:19,375 --> 00:19:24,333
I mean, Michel and Mom,
they have real... real--

334
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,708
[WALLACE]
Don't come in here! Get out!

335
00:19:37,375 --> 00:19:39,375
Um, I, uh...

336
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:42,833
Sorry--

337
00:19:42,916 --> 00:19:48,333
[NICOLAS] I can't read this,
so I'm returning it.

338
00:19:53,375 --> 00:19:56,833
I, uh, guess I never
got your name.

339
00:19:56,916 --> 00:20:00,625
I'm Wallace. Wallace Arcangelo.

340
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:01,916
And you?

341
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,125
[WORICK]
Nic, hold on.

342
00:20:07,208 --> 00:20:08,916
Nicolas!

343
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:13,458
That pile of bodies
they found in District Six

344
00:20:13,541 --> 00:20:15,166
could be his handiwork, too.

345
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:16,958
If so, he's an
unpredictable head case

346
00:20:17,041 --> 00:20:19,416
with no regard for
the Three Laws.

347
00:20:21,875 --> 00:20:23,541
You get that, right?

348
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:26,666
So don't do anything stupid,
you reckless bastard.

349
00:20:35,416 --> 00:20:37,625
[MONROE]
Things are gettin' outta hand.

350
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:49,083
No! Boss!

351
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:50,291
[DOUG]
Gotcha!

352
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:58,791
[DOUG] Quick moves.
But I nicked you, too.

353
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,375
[DOUG]
Ah, so that's it.

354
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:04,458
I knew there was somethin'
off about you earlier.

355
00:21:04,541 --> 00:21:07,250
You wear the tags, but
you don't show 'em off.

356
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:08,750
Plus, you're weak.

357
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:12,125
For real, the great Monroe
family hires only one Twilight,

358
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:14,041
and it's a chickenshit like you?

359
00:21:14,125 --> 00:21:17,666
[MONROE] Hey, even a Low like
this one can serve a purpose.

360
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:21,166
For instance,
he makes a good shield.

361
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:25,000
Hmm... But I don't
remember sayin' that.

362
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:26,250
[gasps]

363
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:29,416
About us havin' only one
Twilight on our payroll.

364
00:21:34,416 --> 00:21:35,458
Nico!

365
00:21:35,541 --> 00:21:36,833
[MILES]
Handyman!

366
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:43,541
[DOUG]
Son of a bitch.

367
00:21:48,416 --> 00:21:50,291
You boys have seen some
shit workin' for me,

368
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:53,458
but you've never seen two guys
ranked this high go at it.

369
00:21:53,541 --> 00:21:55,375
This oughta be fun.

370
00:21:55,458 --> 00:21:57,375
[BOTH]
Boss, should we--?

371
00:22:06,708 --> 00:22:10,500
[MONROE] All right, gents.
Time to place your bets.

372
00:22:12,916 --> 00:22:14,791
[MONROE]
Who's your money on?

